                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4112Anti-War/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-03T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>112. Your 122, May 2, 6 p.m. I have heard nothing about either a commission of
                    technical experts or a conference of Foreign Secretaries. If I do, I shall
                    endeavor to discourage their adoption.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
